# Live Video Color Detector

This program captures a live video feed from the webcam and displays the RGB color values of the pixel under the mouse pointer in real-time. It can be helpful for color analysis in live video applications.

## How It Works
1. Open a video feed from your default webcam.
2. As you move the mouse over the video feed, the RGB color values of the pixel under the pointer are displayed on the screen.
3. To close the program, press `q` on your keyboard.

## Instructions
1. Open a terminal and navigate to the `live_video_color_detector` folder.
2. Run the script with the following command:
   ```bash
   python live_color_detector.py
